            <title>[KAFKA-1544] LogCleaner may take a long time to shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1544</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have the following code in LogCleaner. Since the cleaner thread is shutdown w/o interrupt. If may take up to backoff time for the cleaner thread to detect the shutdown flag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    private def cleanOrSleep() {&lt;br/&gt;
      cleanerManager.grabFilthiestLog() match {&lt;br/&gt;
        case None =&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
          // there are no cleanable logs, sleep a while&lt;br/&gt;
          time.sleep(config.backOffMs)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
